==Events== * [[418]] &ndash; A papal conclave begins, resulting in the election of [[Pope Boniface I]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Claudio Rendina|title=The Popes: Histories and Secrets|url=https://archive.org/details/popes0000rend|url-access=registration|year=2002|publisher=Seven Locks Press|isbn=978-1-931643-13-9|page=[https://archive.org/details/popes0000rend/page/n77 60]}}</ref> * [[457]] &ndash; [[Majorian]] is acclaimed emperor of the [[Western Roman Empire]] and recognized by Emperor [[Leo I the Thracian]]. * [[484]] &ndash; [[Alaric II]] succeeds his father [[Euric]] and becomes king of the [[Visigoths]]. He establishes his capital at [[Aire-sur-l'Adour]] (Southern [[Gaul]]). * [[893]] &ndash; An earthquake [[893 Dvin earthquake|destroys]] the city of [[Dvin (ancient city)|Dvin]], [[Armenia]]. *[[1065]] &ndash; [[Edward the Confessor]]'s [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] monastic church at [[Westminster Abbey]] is [[Consecration|consecrated]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.british-history.ac.uk/rchme/london/vol1/pp1-13|title='Introduction', An Inventory of the Historical Monuments in London, Volume 1, Westminster Abbey|last=|first=|date=|website=British History Online|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 December 2018}}</ref> *[[1308]] &ndash; The reign of [[Emperor Hanazono]] of Japan begins. *[[1659]] &ndash; The [[Maratha Empire|Marathas]] defeat the [[Adil Shahi dynasty|Adilshahi]] forces in the [[Battle of Kolhapur]]. *[[1768]] &ndash; King [[Taksin]]'s coronation achieved through conquest as a king of [[Thailand]] and established [[Thonburi]] as a capital. *[[1795]] &ndash; Construction of [[Yonge Street]], formerly recognized as the longest street in the world, begins in [[York, Upper Canada]] (present-day [[Toronto]]). *[[1832]] &ndash; [[John C. Calhoun]] becomes the first [[Vice President of the United States]] to resign. *[[1835]] &ndash; [[Osceola]] leads his [[Seminole]] warriors in [[Florida]] into the [[Second Seminole War]] against the United States Army. *[[1836]] &ndash; [[South Australia]] and [[Adelaide]] are founded. * 1836 &ndash; Spain recognizes the independence of Mexico with the signing of the [[Spanish attempts to reconquer Mexico|Santa María–Calatrava Treaty]]. *[[1846]] &ndash; [[Iowa]] is admitted as the 29th [[U.S. state]]. *[[1879]] &ndash; [[Tay Bridge disaster]]: The central part of the [[Tay Rail Bridge]] in [[Dundee]], Scotland, United Kingdom collapses as a train passes over it, killing 75. *[[1885]] &ndash; [[Indian National Congress]], a political party of India, is founded in [[Bombay Presidency]], British India. *[[1895]] &ndash; The [[Auguste and Louis Lumière|Lumière brothers]] perform for their first paying audience at the Grand Cafe in ''Boulevard des Capucines''. * 1895 &ndash; [[Wilhelm Röntgen]] publishes a paper detailing his discovery of a new type of [[radiation]], which later will be known as [[x-ray]]s. *[[1902]] &ndash; The [[Syracuse Pros|Syracuse Athletic Club]] [[World Series of Football (1902–03)|defeated]] the [[New York (World Series of Football)|New York Philadelphians]], 5–0, in the [[indoor American football|first indoor professional football]] game, which was held at [[Madison Square Garden (1890)|Madison Square Garden]]. *[[1908]] &ndash; The 7.1 {{M|w}} [[1908 Messina earthquake|Messina earthquake]] shakes [[Southern Italy]] with a maximum [[Mercalli intensity scale|Mercalli intensity]] of XI (''Extreme''), killing between 75,000 and 200,000. *[[1912]] &ndash; The first [[San Francisco Municipal Railway|municipally owned]] [[Tram|streetcar]]s take to the streets in [[San Francisco]]. *[[1918]] &ndash; [[Constance Markievicz]], while detained in Holloway prison, became the first woman to be elected [[Member of parliament#United Kingdom|MP]] to the [[House of Commons of the United Kingdom|British House of Commons]]. *[[1941]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Operation Anthropoid]], the plot to assassinate high-ranking [[Nazism|Nazi]] officer [[Reinhard Heydrich]], commences. *[[1943]] &ndash; Soviet authorities launch Operation Ulussy, beginning the [[Kalmyk deportations of 1943|deportation of the Kalmyk nation]] to Siberia and Central Asia. *1943 &ndash; [[World War II]]: After eight days of brutal [[urban warfare|house-to-house fighting]], the [[Battle of Ortona]] concludes with the victory of the [[1st Canadian Infantry Division]] over the [[1st Parachute Division (Germany)|German 1st Parachute Division]] and the capture of the Italian town of [[Ortona]]. *[[1944]] &ndash; [[Maurice Richard]] becomes the first player to score eight points in one game of [[National Hockey League|NHL]] [[ice hockey]]. *[[1948]] &ndash; The [[Douglas DC-3|DC-3]] airliner ''[[1948 Airborne Transport DC-3 (DST) disappearance|NC16002]]'' disappears 50 miles south of [[Miami]]. *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Chin Peng]], [[David Marshall (Singaporean politician)|David Marshall]] and [[Tunku Abdul Rahman]] meet in [[Baling]], [[Federation of Malaya|Malaya]] to [[Baling Talks|try and resolve]] the [[Malayan Emergency]] situation. *[[1958]] &ndash; [[1958 NFL Championship Game|"Greatest Game Ever Played"]]: [[History of the Indianapolis Colts|Baltimore Colts]] defeat the [[New York Giants]] in the first ever [[National Football League]] [[sudden death (sport)|sudden death]] [[Overtime (sports)|overtime]] game at New York's [[Yankee Stadium (1923)|Yankee Stadium]]. *[[1973]] &ndash; The [[United States]] [[Endangered Species Act]] is signed into law by Pres. [[Richard Nixon]]. *[[1989]] &ndash; A [[1989 Newcastle earthquake|magnitude 5.6 earthquake]] hits [[Newcastle, New South Wales]], Australia, killing 13 people. *[[2006]] &ndash; [[War in Somalia (2006–09)|War in Somalia]]: The militaries of [[Somalia]]'s [[Transitional Federal Parliament|Transitional Federal Government]] and [[Ethiopia]]n troops [[Fall of Mogadishu|capture Mogadishu]] unopposed. *[[2009]] &ndash; [[2009 Karachi bombing|Forty-three people die in a suicide bombing]] in [[Karachi]], Pakistan, where [[Shia Islam|Shia]] Muslims are observing the [[Day of Ashura]]. *[[2014]] &ndash; [[Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501]] crashes into the [[Karimata Strait]] en route from [[Juanda International Airport|Surabaya]] to [[Singapore Changi Airport|Singapore]], killing all 162 people aboard. * 2014 &ndash; Nine people die and another 19 are reported missing, when the [[MS Norman Atlantic|MS ''Norman Atlantic'']] catches fire in the [[Strait of Otranto]], in the [[Adriatic Sea]], in Italian waters.
